==English==

===Etymology===
From the Italian ''[[milione]]'' (''million''), from ''[[mille]]'' (''thousand''), from the Latin ''[[mille]]'' + the augmentative suffix ''[[-one]]''.

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˈmɪljən/}}, {{SAMPA|/"mIlj@n/}}
*{{audio|en-gb-million.ogg|Audio (RP)}}
*{{audio|en-us-million.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*{{rhymes|ɪljən}}
*Hyphenation: mil·lion

===Cardinal number===
'''million'''

# (''[[w:Long and short scales|long and short scales]]'') The cardinal number 1,000,000: 10<sup>6</sup>. Ordinal: [[millionth]].

*''Western (Arabic) Numeral'' '''million, 10<sup>6</sup>'''
**'''Previous''': [[w:Long and short scales|long and short scales]]: [[thousand]], 1,000
**'''Next''': [[w:Long and short scales|short scale]]: [[billion]], 10<sup>9</sup>; [[w:Long and short scales|long scale]]: [[milliard]], 10<sup>9</sup>
*Symbolic: 10<sup>6</sup> = 1,000,000
*ISO prefix: [[mega-]]

